 summary statistics (Min/1stQu/Median/Mean/\n    3rdQu/Max plus `num_peaks`, `measure`, `sample`) for `fold`, `-log10(qvalue)`,\n    `-log10(pvalue)`, and `length` (end-start).\n  - `macs_qc.pdf`: a multi-page PDF with the peak count barplot and three violin\n    plots (length on log10, fold on log2, FDR / pvalue on linear -log10).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/macs_qc.pdf` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: macs_qc.pdf, macs_qc_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/macs_qc.pdf` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_K9xz3ZjnCt9HyVRmruWI9gts", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the three narrowPeak files from the input directory.\\n2. Extract relevant columns: fold, -log10(qvalue), -log10(pvalue), and calculate length (end-start).\\n3. Compute summary statistics for each sample and each measure.\\n4. Write the summary statistics to 'output/macs_qc_summary.tsv'.\\n5. Create a multi-page PDF with:\\n   - A barplot of peak counts for each sample.\\n   - Violin plots for length (log10), fold (log2), and FDR/pvalue (-log10).\\n6. Save the PDF as 'output/macs_qc.pdf'.\\n7. Verify the existence of the output files and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_pl